oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Foute House
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Edwin Best
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: Greenback (Tenn.); Blankenship, M.; Foute, E.J.; Wilson, A.J.; Kerr, Jesse; Beals, Allen;
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Woman in yard of house. She has on a light-colored blouse with some decorative detail and a dark-colored skirt. A boy with a large hat is looking out from behind her. The house has clapboard siding, wooden shingles and a corner porch with some decorative trim. Some young trees are in the yard. It might be Miss Mal [?] Blankenship in front of Foute House.
